rComments: The course consists of the students doing research for the projects on which she is currently working on as part of her job at the ROM. She does not lecture, she assigns hundreds of pages of readings and then 'discusses' them in class, which is what 15% of your grade is on. I participated a LOT in these discussion yet I got a B in participation?!
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Graded by few things', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: This course has 15% allocation to attendance. I received 80+ in all my assignments, but i did not have good rapport with the instructor. She gave me 70% on my class participation. I had missed only two classes. I was always very active during classes and participated heavily.  The class participation is her opportunity to decide who she favours..

Very difficult grader; I am a student that routinely received 85+ in my courses and I received a B+ in this one.  She is, unfortunately not trained to teach and so fails to both communicate her expectations clearly and to put students' work in perspective. 200 page readings assigned and no guidance as to what to look for in them, the theme, etc.
Not worth one's time and trouble. Basically doing research for her own personal gain.
